description:
Navajo First Phase Silver and Turquoise Concha Belt 
fourth quarter 19th century

seven oval-shaped silver conchas with scalloped edges decorated with stamping and diamond-shaped cutouts, accented with intertwined stamped design; rectangular buckle, set with two turquoise cabochons and accented with repoussé; not marked

belt length 45 inches;
concha length 4-3/8 inches x width 3-1/2 inches;
buckle length 3-1/4 inches x width 3 inches;
weight 607.2 dwt.


The Collection of Michelle Smith, Washington, D.C.

